reviews.review_text: Great sounding Aud. recording Great sound! The better of the two recordings on Llama.
Smell the Weg! This right here is the Grateful Dead playing in your garage at the peak of their playing abilities.

Never before, never again... ...were the Dead able to pull off a stealth show like this.  The Melkweg's rear balcony is about 20 feet from the stage, if that.  15 people in this tiny room, and I got there eight years too late.

I just played the Rhythm Devils > Phil bottleneck > Other One on the radio today, from this source.  Got a lot of calls of appreciation.  Thanks, Michel!

Inspiration on display Ragged but ultimately right, this show is a showcase for the Dead having an evening of sloppy, inspired fun. The recording is quite acceptable and the audience sounds wonderfully responsive to the music - listen to the roar of approval that greets "Althea".

Highlights: "Minglewood", "Althea", "Man Smart", "He's Gone", "Spoonful".

Smell it indeed Wowee! Talk about intimate! This is just downright weird. Another gem for the collection from archive.org. Thanks folks! I'm goin' 5 just for the "off-the-beaten-track" factor on this one. Well, and the Phil bottle neck solo. "Rock and Roll!"
